{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882176502,"sessionID":"ses_2852e7c8dffe11nduLnctiZJZf","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad3877e001UYZAC3u1DlP1uA","messageID":"msg_d7ad20f1c001erZ3qdqjmc45Kt","sessionID":"ses_2852e7c8dffe11nduLnctiZJZf","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-488e0aefff9440988fbd2a9d6cdc4ea5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-031: RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) — Design\n\n## Overview\n\nAR-031 defines the Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) configuration for the AgentCube platform. This module provides ServiceAccount, Role/ClusterRole, and RoleBinding/ClusterRoleBinding resources for all platform components (controller-manager, workload-manager, router). The RBAC configuration ensures proper permission boundaries for each component while maintaining flexibility for custom deployments.\n\n**Module:** `manifests`  \n**Language:** YAML (Helm templates)  \n**Source Root:** `/manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/`\n\n## Architecture\n\n### RBAC Hierarchy\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        AgentCube Namespace                       │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                  │\n│  Controller-Manager          Workload-Manager         Router     │\n│  ┌──────────────┐           ┌──────────────┐       ┌───────────┐ │\n│  │ ServiceAcc   │           │ ServiceAcc   │       │ Service   │ │\n│  │ - name       │           │ - name       │       │ Account   │ │\n│  │ - annotations│           │ - annotations│       │           │ │\n│  └──────┬───────┘           └──────┬───────┘       └─────┬─────┘ │\n│         │                          │                     │       │\n│         │ RoleBinding              │ ClusterRoleBinding │ Role    │\n│         │ → Role                   │ → ClusterRole      │ Binding │\n│         │                          │ (cluster-wide)     │ → Role  │\n│         └──────────────┬───────────┘                    └─────┬───┘ │\n│                        │                                      │     │\n│                        │              Custom Rules           │     │\n│                        │         (via values.yaml)           │     │\n│                        └──────────────────────────────────────┘     │\n└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Cluster-Wide Resources                        │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  ClusterRole (workload-manager)                                  │\n│  - runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh resources (get/list/watch/...)  │\n│  - pods, services, configmaps, secrets (get/list/watch/...)     │\n│  - pods/status (get)                                             │\n│  - events (create/patch)                                         │\n└───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Components\n\n| Component | Location | Responsibility |\n|-----------|----------|----------------|\n| ServiceAccount Templates | `templates/*/serviceaccount.yaml` | Identity for each component pod |\n| Role Templates | `templates/*/rbac.yaml` | Namespace-scoped permissions |\n| ClusterRole Template | `templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml` | Cluster-scoped permissions |\n| RoleBinding Templates | `templates/*/rbac.yaml` | Bind SAs to namespace Roles |\n| ClusterRoleBinding Template | `templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml` | Bind SA to cluster-wide Role |\n| Helper Templates | `templates/_helpers.tpl` | Name generation logic |\n\n### Permission Scope\n\n| Component | Resource Scope | Required APIs |\n|-----------|----------------|---------------|\n| controller-manager | Namespace (empty by default) | Custom rules via `values.controllerManager.rbac.rules` |\n| workload-manager | Cluster | CRDs, pods, services, configmaps, secrets, events |\n| router | Namespace | Secrets only |\n\n## Detailed Implementation\n\n### 1. ServiceAccount Templates\n\n#### Controller-Manager ServiceAccount\n\n**Location:** `templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n{{- if and .Values.controllerManager.enabled .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.create }}\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.controllerManager.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\n  {{- with .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.annotations }}\n  annotations:\n    {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n  {{- end }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n**Configuration:**\n- Enabled when `controllerManager.enabled` and `controllerManager.serviceAccount.create` are true\n- Name: Full chart name (default) or `controllerManager.serviceAccount.name` override\n- Labels: Standard chart labels + component label\n- Annotations: From `controllerManager.serviceAccount.annotations`\n\n#### Workload-Manager ServiceAccount\n\n**Location:** `templates/workload-manager/serviceaccount.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n{{- if and .Values.workloadManager.enabled .Values.workloadManager.serviceAccount.create }}\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.workloadManager.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: workload-manager\n  {{- with .Values.workloadManager.serviceAccount.annotations }}\n  annotations:\n    {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n  {{- end }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n**Configuration:**\n- Name: `{fullname}-workload-manager` (default) or override\n- Requires cluster-wide permissions via ClusterRoleBinding\n\n#### Router ServiceAccount\n\n**Location:** `templates/router/serviceaccount.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n{{- if and .Values.router.enabled .Values.router.serviceAccount.create }}\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.router.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: router\n  {{- with .Values.router.serviceAccount.annotations }}\n  annotations:\n    {{- toYaml . | nindent 4 }}\n  {{- end }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n**Configuration:**\n- Name: `{fullname}-router` (default) or override\n- Minimal permissions: only secrets access\n\n### 2. Role Templates\n\n#### Controller-Manager Role\n\n**Location:** `templates/controller-manager/rbac.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n{{- if and .Values.controllerManager.enabled .Values.controllerManager.rbac.create }}\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: Role\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\nrules:\n{{- if .Values.controllerManager.rbac.rules }}\n{{- toYaml .Values.controllerManager.rbac.rules | nindent 2 }}\n{{- else }}\n  []\n{{- end }}\n---\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: RoleBinding\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: controller-manager\nroleRef:\n  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n  kind: Role\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\nsubjects:\n- kind: ServiceAccount\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.controllerManager.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n**Features:**\n- Empty rules by default (controller-manager may not need namespace-scoped permissions)\n- Custom rules via `controllerManager.rbac.rules`\n- RoleBinding binds ServiceAccount to Role in same namespace\n\n#### Router Role\n\n**Location:** `templates/router/rbac.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n{{- if and .Values.router.enabled .Values.router.rbac.create }}\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: Role\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: router\nrules:\n- apiGroups:\n  - \"\"\n  resources:\n  - secrets\n  verbs:\n  - get\n  - list\n  - watch\n---\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: RoleBinding\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: router\nroleRef:\n  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n  kind: Role\n  name: {{ printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\nsubjects:\n- kind: ServiceAccount\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.router.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n**Features:**\n- Read-only access to secrets (get/list/watch)\n- Used for reading configuration secrets in router namespace\n\n### 3. ClusterRole Template\n\n#### Workload-Manager ClusterRole\n\n**Location:** `templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml`\n\n```yaml\n{{- if and .Values.workloadManager.enabled .Values.workloadManager.rbac.create }}\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRole\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ printf \"%s-workload-manager\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: workload-manager\nrules:\n{{- toYaml .Values.rbac.clusterRole.rules | nindent 0 }}\n---\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRoleBinding\nmetadata:\n  name: {{ printf \"%s-workload-manager\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\n  labels:\n    {{- include \"agentcube.labels\" . | nindent 4 }}\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: workload-manager\nroleRef:\n  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n  kind: ClusterRole\n  name: {{ printf \"%s-workload-manager\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) }}\nsubjects:\n- kind: ServiceAccount\n  name: {{ include \"agentcube.workloadManager.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n  namespace: {{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n**Rules Configuration (from `values.yaml`):**\n\n```yaml\nrbac:\n  clusterRole:\n    rules:\n    - apiGroups:\n      - runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n      resources:\n      - agentruntimes\n      - codeinterpreters\n      verbs:\n      - get\n      - list\n      - watch\n      - create\n      - update\n      - patch\n      - delete\n    - apiGroups:\n      - runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n      resources:\n      - agentruntimes/status\n      - codeinterpreters/status\n      verbs:\n      - get\n      - update\n      - patch\n    - apiGroups:\n      - \"\"\n      resources:\n      - pods\n      - services\n      - configmaps\n      - secrets\n      verbs:\n      - get\n      - list\n      - watch\n      - create\n      - update\n      - patch\n      - delete\n    - apiGroups:\n      - \"\"\n      resources:\n      - pods/status\n      verbs:\n      - get\n    - apiGroups:\n      - \"\"\n      resources:\n      - events\n      verbs:\n      - create\n      - patch\n```\n\n**Permission Breakdown:**\n- CRD resources (agentruntimes, codeinterpreters): Full CRUD + status\n- Workload resources (pods, services, configmaps, secrets): Full CRUD\n- Pod status: Read-only\n- Events: Create and patch (for event recording)\n\n### 4. Helper Templates\n\n#### ServiceAccount Name Helpers\n\n```yaml\n{{- define \"agentcube.controllerManager.serviceAccountName\" -}}\n{{- if .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.create }}\n{{- default (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .) .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.name }}\n{{- else }}\n{{- default \"default\" .Values.controllerManager.serviceAccount.name }}\n{{- end }}\n{{- end }}\n\n{{- define \"agentcube.workloadManager.serviceAccountName\" -}}\n{{- if .Values.workloadManager.serviceAccount.create }}\n{{- default (printf \"%s-workload-manager\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .)) .Values.workloadManager.serviceAccount.name }}\n{{- else }}\n{{- default \"default\" .Values.workloadManager.serviceAccount.name }}\n{{- end }}\n{{- end }}\n\n{{- define \"agentcube.router.serviceAccountName\" -}}\n{{- if .Values.router.serviceAccount.create }}\n{{- default (printf \"%s-router\" (include \"agentcube.fullname\" .)) .Values.router.serviceAccount.name }}\n{{- else }}\n{{- default \"default\" .Values.router.serviceAccount.name }}\n{{- end }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n**Logic:**\n- If creating ServiceAccount: use provided name or generate default\n- If using existing ServiceAccount: use provided name or \"default\"\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Values Configuration\n\n```yaml\n# ServiceAccount configuration\ncontrollerManager:\n  enabled: true\n  serviceAccount:\n    create: true\n    name: \"\"\n    annotations:\n      example-annotation: value\n  rbac:\n    create: true\n    rules: []\n\nworkloadManager:\n  enabled: true\n  serviceAccount:\n    create: true\n    name: \"\"\n    annotations: {}\n  rbac:\n    create: true\n    rules: []\n\nrouter:\n  enabled: true\n  serviceAccount:\n    create: true\n    name: \"\"\n    annotations: {}\n  rbac:\n    create: true\n    rules: []\n\n# Global RBAC configuration\nrbac:\n  create: true\n  clusterRole:\n    create: true\n    rules:\n    # CRD permissions\n    - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n      resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n      verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n    # CRD status permissions\n    - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n      resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\", \"codeinterpreters/status\"]\n      verbs: [\"get\", \"update\", \"patch\"]\n    # Core resources\n    - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n      resources: [\"pods\", \"services\", \"configmaps\", \"secrets\"]\n      verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n    # Pod status\n    - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n      resources: [\"pods/status\"]\n      verbs: [\"get\"]\n    # Events\n    - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n      resources: [\"events\"]\n      verbs: [\"create\", \"patch\"]\n```\n\n### Kubernetes Resource Specifications\n\n#### ServiceAccount\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: ServiceAccount\nmetadata:\n  name: string\n  namespace: string\n  labels:\n    helm.sh/chart: string\n    app.kubernetes.io/name: string\n    app.kubernetes.io/instance: string\n    app.kubernetes.io/version: string\n    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: string\n    app.kubernetes.io/component: string\n  annotations:\n    # Custom annotations from values\n```\n\n#### Role\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: Role\nmetadata:\n  name: string\n  namespace: string\n  labels: {}\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"\"]  # Core API group is \"\"\n  resources: [\"pods\", \"services\", \"configmaps\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n```\n\n#### ClusterRole\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRole\nmetadata:\n  name: string\n  labels: {}\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"create\", \"update\", \"patch\", \"delete\"]\n```\n\n#### RoleBinding\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: RoleBinding\nmetadata:\n  name: string\n  namespace: string\n  labels: {}\nroleRef:\n  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n  kind: Role\n  name: string\nsubjects:\n- kind: ServiceAccount\n  name: string\n  namespace: string\n```\n\n#### ClusterRoleBinding\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRoleBinding\nmetadata:\n  name: string\n  labels: {}\nroleRef:\n  apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io\n  kind: ClusterRole\n  name: string\nsubjects:\n- kind: ServiceAccount\n  name: string\n  namespace: string\n```\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Kubernetes RBAC API\n\n#### API Groups and Resources\n\n| API Group | Version | Resources | Verbs |\n|-----------|---------|-----------|-------|\n| `rbac.authorization.k8s.io` | v1 | roles, rolebindings, clusterroles, clusterrolebindings | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete |\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | v1alpha1 | agentruntimes, codeinterpreters | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete |\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | v1alpha1 | agentruntimes/status, codeinterpreters/status | get, update, patch |\n| `` (core) | v1 | pods, services, configmaps, secrets | get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete |\n| `` (core) | v1 | pods/status | get |\n| `` (core) | v1 | events | create, patch |\n\n#### ServiceAccount Authentication\n\nPods using a ServiceAccount automatically receive:\n- Mounted token at `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n- Mounted CA certificate at `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/ca.crt`\n- API server reference at `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/namespace`\n\nThe Workload Manager uses this token to authenticate to the Kubernetes API.\n\n### Helm Template API\n\n#### Template Variables\n\n| Variable | Type | Description |\n|----------|------|-------------|\n| `.Values.component.enabled` | bool | Component enable flag |\n| `.Values.component.serviceAccount.create` | bool | Create SA or use existing |\n| `.Values.component.serviceAccount.name` | string | SA name override |\n| `.Values.component.serviceAccount.annotations` | dict | SA annotations |\n| `.Values.component.rbac.create` | bool | Create RBAC resources |\n| `.Values.component.rbac.rules` | list | Custom Role rules |\n| `.Values.rbac.clusterRole.rules` | list | ClusterRole rules |\n| `.Values.global.namespaceOverride` | string | Namespace override |\n| `.Chart.Name` | string | Chart name |\n| `.Chart.Version` | string | Chart version |\n| `.Release.Name` | string | Release name |\n| `.Release.Namespace` | string | Release namespace |\n\n#### Template Functions\n\n```yaml\n# Standard chart name\n{{ include \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}\n\n# Component-specific SA names\n{{ include \"agentcube.controllerManager.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n{{ include \"agentcube.workloadManager.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n{{ include \"agentcube.router.serviceAccountName\" . }}\n\n# Namespace resolution\n{{ include \"agentcube.namespace\" . }}\n\n# Standard labels\n{{ include \"agentcube.labels\" . }}\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Validation Errors\n\n#### Missing Configuration\n\n**Scenario:** Component enabled but RBAC disabled\n\n**Validation:** \n```yaml\n{{- if and .Values.component.enabled (not .Values.component.rbac.create) }}\n{{- fail \"Component enabled but RBAC creation disabled\" }}\n{{- end }}\n```\n\n**User Message:**\n```\nError: component enabled but RBAC creation disabled\nPlease set component.rbac.create to true or disable the component\n```\n\n#### Invalid ServiceAccount Name\n\n**Scenario:** ServiceAccount name exceeds 253 characters\n\n**Prevention:** Helm truncates names to 63 characters via `| trunc 63 | trimSuffix \"-\"`\n\n#### Invalid RBAC Rules\n\n**Scenario:** Invalid verbs or API groups in custom rules\n\n**Prevention:** Kubernetes API server validates rules at resource creation\n\n**Error Response:**\n```\nError: failed to create rolebinding: Role.rbac.authorization.k8s.io \"name\" is invalid: rules[0].verbs[0]: Unsupported value: \"invalidverb\"\n```\n\n### Deployment Errors\n\n#### ServiceAccount Not Found\n\n**Scenario:** Using existing ServiceAccount that doesn't exist\n\n**Error:** Pod fails to start with admission error\n\n**User Action:** Create the ServiceAccount or set `serviceAccount.create: true`\n\n```\nWarning  FailedCreate  5m  replicaset  Error creating: pods \"xyz\" is forbidden:\nerror looking up service account component/xyz: serviceaccount \"xyz\" not found\n```\n\n#### Permission Denied\n\n**Scenario:** Component lacks required permissions\n\n**Error:** Application logs show 403 Forbidden from Kubernetes API\n\n**Example:**\n```\nE0411 12:00:00.000000       1 runtime.go:78] Failed to list pods:\npods is forbidden: User \"system:serviceaccount:agentcube:workload-manager\"\ncannot list resource \"pods\" in API group \"\" at the cluster scope\n```\n\n**Troubleshooting:**\n1. Verify ServiceAccount is bound to correct Role/ClusterRole\n2. Verify Role/ClusterRole has required rules\n3. Verify ClusterRoleBinding references correct namespace\n\n#### RBAC Policy Too Permissive\n\n**Scenario:** Custom rules grant excessive permissions\n\n**Prevention:** Document required permissions in `values.yaml` comments\n\n**Recommendation:** Use specific verbs instead of wildcard `*`\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### Template Rendering Tests\n\n**Test File:** `manifests/charts/agentcube/tests/rbac_test.yaml`\n\n```yaml\nsuite: Test RBAC Configuration\ntemplates:\n  - templates/controller-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n  - templates/workload-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n  - templates/router/serviceaccount.yaml\n  - templates/controller-manager/rbac.yaml\n  - templates/workload-manager/rbac.yaml\n  - templates/router/rbac.yaml\ntests:\n  - it: Creates all RBAC resources when enabled\n    set:\n      controllerManager.enabled: true\n      workloadManager.enabled: true\n      router.enabled: true\n      controllerManager.serviceAccount.create: true\n      workloadManager.serviceAccount.create: true\n      router.serviceAccount.create: true\n      controllerManager.rbac.create: true\n      workloadManager.rbac.create: true\n      router.rbac.create: true\n    asserts:\n      - isKind:\n          of: ServiceAccount\n      - isKind:\n          of: Role\n      - isKind:\n          of: RoleBinding\n      - isKind:\n          of: ClusterRole\n      - isKind:\n          of: ClusterRoleBinding\n\n  - it: Skips RBAC creation when disabled\n    set:\n      controllerManager.rbac.create: false\n    asserts:\n      - hasDocuments:\n          count: 0\n\n  - it: Uses existing ServiceAccount when create is false\n    set:\n      controllerManager.serviceAccount.create: false\n      controllerManager.serviceAccount.name: existing-sa\n    asserts:\n      - hasDocuments:\n          count: 0\n\n  - it: Applies custom RBAC rules for controller-manager\n    set:\n      controllerManager.rbac.rules:\n        - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n          resources: [\"configmaps\"]\n          verbs: [\"get\"]\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: rules[0].resources\n          value: [\"configmaps\"]\n      - equal:\n          path: rules[0].verbs\n          value: [\"get\"]\n\n  - it: Router Role has only secrets permission\n    asserts:\n      - equal:\n          path: rules[0].resources\n          value: [\"secrets\"]\n      - equal:\n          path: rules[0].verbs\n          value: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\"]\n\n  - it: Workload Manager ClusterRole has CRD permissions\n    asserts:\n      - contains:\n          path: rules\n          content:\n            apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n            resources: [\"agentruntimes\", \"codeinterpreters\"]\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n#### Permission Verification\n\n**Test 1: Verify Workload Manager Can Create Pods**\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# Test: Workload Manager can create pods\nkubectl auth can-i create pods \\\n  --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-workload-manager \\\n  -n agentcube\n# Expected: yes\n```\n\n**Test 2: Verify Router Can List Secrets**\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# Test: Router can list secrets\nkubectl auth can-i list secrets \\\n  --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-router \\\n  -n agentcube\n# Expected: yes\n```\n\n**Test 3: Verify Controller Manager Cannot Delete Pods**\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# Test: Controller manager cannot delete pods (by default)\nkubectl auth can-i delete pods \\\n  --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube \\\n  -n agentcube\n# Expected: no (if no custom rules)\n```\n\n#### End-to-End Tests\n\n**Test 1: Deploy AgentCube with Custom RBAC**\n\n```yaml\n# test-values.yaml\ncontrollerManager:\n  rbac:\n    rules:\n      - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n        resources: [\"configmaps\"]\n        verbs: [\"get\", \"list\"]\n```\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# Test deployment with custom RBAC\nhelm install agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube \\\n  -f test-values.yaml \\\n  --namespace agentcube \\\n  --create-namespace\n\n# Verify Role has custom rules\nkubectl get role agentcube -n agentcube -o yaml | grep -A 5 \"resources:\"\n\n# Clean up\nhelm uninstall agentcube -n agentcube\n```\n\n**Test 2: Deploy with Existing ServiceAccount**\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# Test: Use existing ServiceAccount\nkubectl create serviceaccount existing-router -n agentcube\n\nhelm install agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube \\\n  --set router.serviceAccount.create=false \\\n  --set router.serviceAccount.name=existing-router \\\n  --namespace agentcube\n\n# Verify Router uses existing SA\nkubectl get deployment agentcube-router -n agentcube \\\n  -o jsonpath='{.spec.template.spec.serviceAccountName}'\n\n# Expected: existing-router\n```\n\n### Security Tests\n\n**Test 1: Principle of Least Privilege**\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# Test: Verify minimal permissions\ncomponents=(\"controller-manager\" \"workload-manager\" \"router\")\n\nfor component in \"${components[@]}\"; do\n  sa_name=\"agentcube-${component//manager/manager}\"\n  echo \"Testing $component permissions...\"\n  \n  # Get all permissions\n  kubectl auth can-i \"*\" \"*\" \\\n    --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:$sa_name \\\n    --all-namespaces \\\n    2>&1 | grep -i \"no\"\ndone\n```\n\n**Test 2: No Wildcard Permissions**\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# Test: Verify no wildcard (*) verbs\nfor role in $(kubectl get roles -n agentcube -o name); do\n  echo \"Checking $role for wildcard verbs...\"\n  kubectl get $role -n agentcube -o yaml | grep -i \"verbs:\\s*-\\s*[*]\"\n  if [ $? -eq 0 ]; then\n    echo \"WARNING: Wildcard verb found in $role\"\n  fi\ndone\n```\n\n**Test 3: ServiceAccount Token Automount**\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# Test: Verify token automount is controlled\nfor deployment in $(kubectl get deployments -n agentcube -o name); do\n  echo \"Checking $deployment...\"\n  kubectl get $deployment -n agentcube -o yaml \\\n    | grep -A 5 \"automountServiceAccountToken\"\ndone\n```\n\n### Performance Tests\n\n**Test 1: RBAC Evaluation Performance**\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# Test: Measure RBAC evaluation time\ntime kubectl auth can-i get pods \\\n  --as=system:serviceaccount:agentcube:agentcube-workload-manager \\\n  -n agentcube\n```\n\n**Test 2: Large Scale RBAC**\n\n```yaml\n# stress-test-values.yaml\ncontrollerManager:\n  rbac:\n    rules:\n      # Add 100 custom rules\n      {{- range $i := until 100 }}\n      - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n        resources: [\"resource-{{ $i }}\"]\n        verbs: [\"get\"]\n      {{- end }}\n```\n\n```bash\n#!/bin/bash\n# Test: Large scale RBAC configuration\nhelm install agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube \\\n  -f stress-test-values.yaml \\\n  --namespace agentcube\n\n# Measure template render time\ntime helm template agentcube ./manifests/charts/agentcube \\\n  -f stress-test-values.yaml\n```\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### 1. Principle of Least Privilege\n\n- Default RBAC rules provide only necessary permissions\n- Router has minimal permissions (secrets only)\n- Workload Manager requires cluster-wide access but is bounded to specific resources\n- Controller Manager has no default namespace-scoped permissions\n\n### 2. ServiceAccount Security\n\n- Each component uses dedicated ServiceAccount\n- ServiceAccount names follow naming convention\n- Automount of ServiceAccount token can be controlled via `automountServiceAccountToken` in pod spec\n- Tokens are mounted at `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/`\n\n### 3. RBAC Scope Management\n\n- Namespace-scoped: Role, RoleBinding, ServiceAccount\n- Cluster-scoped: ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding\n- Workload Manager is the only component requiring cluster-wide access\n- Router and Controller Manager use namespace-scoped permissions\n\n### 4. Custom Rule Validation\n\nWhen adding custom RBAC rules via `values.yaml`, ensure:\n- Avoid wildcard `*` verbs unless necessary\n- Specify exact API groups and resources\n- Use most restrictive verbs (e.g., `get` instead of `*`)\n- Document the reason for each permission\n\n### 5. Namespace Isolation\n\n- All RBAC resources are namespaced except ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding\n- ServiceAccount namespaced to `agentcube` namespace by default\n- Role bindings only authorize access within the same namespace\n\n## Future Enhancements\n\n1. **Pod Security Policy Support**\n   - Add PSP resources for enhanced pod security\n   - Support for Kubernetes 1.25+ Pod Security Standards\n\n2. **NetworkPolicy RBAC**\n   - Add network policies to restrict inter-component communication\n   - Configure network policies based on RBAC permissions\n\n3. **Dynamic RBAC Management**\n   - Support for dynamic RBAC rule updates without reinstall\n   - RBAC rules as ConfigMaps for easier management\n\n4. **Audit Logging**\n   - Add audit annotations to RBAC resources\n   - Track permission changes over time\n\n5. **Multi-Tenant Support**\n   - Support for multi-tenant RBAC configurations\n   - Namespace-specific RBAC overrides\n\n6. **RBAC Testing Automation**\n   - Automated permission testing in CI/CD\n   - Permission drift detection\n\n7. **ServiceAccount Token Rotation**\n   - Support for token rotation policies\n   - Configurable token expiration\n\n8. **External RBAC Integration**\n   - Support for external authentication providers\n   - OIDC-based service account authentication","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/router/rbac.yaml\">\nERROR [1:3] Block collections are not allowed within flow collections\nERROR [1:5] Missing , or : between flow map items\nERROR [2:1] Unexpected scalar at node end\nERROR [2:11] Unexpected map-value-ind token in YAML stream: \":\"\nERROR [2:13] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\"\nERROR [3:1] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"kind\"\nERROR [3:5] Unexpected map-value-ind token in YAML stream: \":\"\nERROR [3:7] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"Role\"\nERROR [4:1] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"metadata\"\nERROR [4:9] Unexpected map-value-ind token in YAML stream: \":\"\nERROR [5:3] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"name\"\nERROR [5:7] Unexpected map-value-ind token in YAML stream: \":\"\nERROR [5:9] Unexpected flow-map-start token in YAML stream: \"{\"\nERROR [5:10] Unexpected flow-map-start token in YAML stream: \"{\"\nERROR [5:12] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"printf \\\"%s-router\\\" (include \\\"agentcube.fullname\\\" .)\"\nERROR [5:64] Unexpected flow-map-end token in YAML stream: \"}\"\nERROR [5:65] Unexpected flow-map-end token in YAML stream: \"}\"\nERROR [6:3] Unexpected scalar token in YAML stream: \"namespace\"\nERROR [6:12] Unexpected map-value-ind token in YAML stream: \":\"\nERROR [6:14] Unexpected flow-map-start token in YAML stream: \"{\"\n... and 41 more\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/manifests/charts/agentcub